<inglise> NOTES that Commission Recommendation 98/257/EC on the principles applicable to the bodies responsible for out-of-court settlement of consumer disputes is an important contribution to the establishment and development of national bodies. </inglise>
<eesti> TUNNISTAB, et komisjoni soovitus 98/257/E&Uuml; tarbijavaidluste kohtuv&auml;lise lahendamise eest vastutavate asutuste suhtes kohaldatavate p&otilde;him&otilde;tete kohta annab olulise panuse siseriiklike organite asutamisse ja arendamisse; </eesti>
<inglise> 7. </inglise>
<eesti> 7. </eesti>
<inglise> NOTES that out-of-court bodies exist in Member States which fall outside the scope of Recommendation 98/257/EC, as they do not formally propose and/or impose a solution, but merely attempt to find a solution by common consent, and which therefore are not expected to apply all the principles established in the Recommendation, but which also play a useful role for the consumer. </inglise>
<eesti> TUNNISTAB, et kohtuv&auml;lised organid eksisteerivad liikmesriikides, mis j&auml;&auml;vad soovituse 98/257/E&Uuml; reguleerimisalast v&auml;lja, kuna nad ei paku ega kehtesta ametlikult lahendust, vaid p&uuml;&uuml;avad j&otilde;uda &uuml;hisele seisukohale, ja seep&auml;rast ei oodata nendelt organitelt k&otilde;ikide soovituses kehtestatud p&otilde;him&otilde;tete kohaldamist, kuid nad on tarbija seisukohalt olulised; </eesti>
<inglise> 8. </inglise>
<eesti> 8. </eesti>
<inglise> WELCOMES the Commission working document on the creation of a European Extra-Judicial Network (EEJ-Net). </inglise>
<eesti> TERVITAB komisjoni t&ouml;&ouml;dokumenti Euroopa kohtuv&auml;lise v&otilde;rgu loomise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> 9. </inglise>
<eesti> 9. </eesti>
<inglise> WELCOMES the Commission's suggestion to include in the EEJ-Net, where appropriate, out-of-court bodies or schemes falling outside the scope of Recommendation 98/257/EC and suggests that Member States see to it that such bodies or schemes apply all the criteria to be developed as outlined in point 11(5). </inglise>
<eesti> TERVITAB komisjoni ettepanekut h&otilde;lmata Euroopa kohtuv&auml;lisesse v&otilde;rku vajaduse korral soovituse 98/257/E&Uuml; reguleerimisalasse mittekuuluvaid kohtuv&auml;liseid organeid v&otilde;i kavasid ning teeb ettepaneku, et liikmesriigid hoolitseksid selle eest, et nende organite v&otilde;i kavade puhul kohaldatakse punkti 11 alapunktis 5 kirjeldatud kriteeriume; </eesti>
<inglise> 10. </inglise>
<eesti> 10. </eesti>
<inglise> INVITES the Member States to: </inglise>
<eesti> KUTSUB liikmesriike &uuml;les: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) encourage the activities of bodies for the out-of-court settlement of consumer disputes, also as regards transborder transactions, and where appropriate, the setting-up of such bodies, on the basis of Recommendation 98/257/EC; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) soodustama tarbijavaidluste kohtuv&auml;lise lahendamise organite tegevust, sealhulgas riikidevaheliste tehingute suhtes, ja vajaduse korral selliste organite asutamist soovituse 98/257/E&Uuml; alusel; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) taking account of point 4 above and in the light of the ongoing discussion among stakeholders, create or designate, in addition, in each Member State a central point (Clearing House) to provide information, guidance, practical support and practical assistance to consumers in order to facilitate their access to the relevant out-of-court bodies or schemes at national level or, where appropriate, in the country of the supplier, as well as to the contact points in other Member States; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) v&otilde;tma arvesse punkti 4 ning looma v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;rama lisaks sellele huvir&uuml;hmade seas toimuvaid arutelusid silmas pidades igas liikmesriigis keskuse (teabeedastuspunkt), mis annaks tarbijatele teavet, juhiseid, praktilist tuge ja abi, et h&otilde;lbustada nende juurdep&auml;&auml;su asjaomastele kohtuv&auml;listele organitele v&otilde;i kavadele siseriiklikul tasandil v&otilde;i vajaduse korral tarnija riigis, ning teistes liikmesriikides asuvatele kontaktpunktidele; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) encourage cooperation between professional and economic organisations and consumer organisations with a view to: </inglise>
<eesti> 3) soodustama koost&ouml;&ouml;d kutse- ja majandusorganisatsioonide ning tarbijaorganisatsioonide vahel, et: </eesti>
<inglise> - contributing to the activities of out-of-court bodies and the contact points, </inglise>
<eesti> - edendada omalt poolt kohtuv&auml;liste organite ja kontaktpunktide tegevust, </eesti>
<inglise> - promoting, in this context, the creation of new dispute settlement schemes, in particular with an on-line application; </inglise>
<eesti> - edendada selles kontekstis vaidluste lahendamise uute kavade loomist, eelk&otilde;ige sidusrakendust kasutades; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) encourage companies, as well as professional and economic organisations, to act in affiliation or association with out-of-court bodies in Member States where they or their members do business with consumers; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) julgustama &auml;ri&uuml;hinguid ning kutse- ja majandusorganisatsioone tegutsema koost&ouml;&ouml;s kohtuv&auml;liste organitega liikmesriikides, kus neil v&otilde;i nende liikmetel on tarbijatega &auml;risuhted; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) communicate to the Commission, if they have not yet done so, the bodies applying the principles of Recommendation 98/257/EC as well as, where appropriate, other out-of-court bodies or schemes. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) teatama komisjonile, kui nad ei ole seda teinud, soovituse 98/257/E&Uuml; p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid kohaldavad organid ning vajaduse korral teised kohtuv&auml;lised organid v&otilde;i kavad; </eesti>
<inglise> 11. </inglise>
<eesti> 11. </eesti>
<inglise> INVITES the Commission to: </inglise>
<eesti> KUTSUB komisjoni &uuml;les: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) assist Member States, where appropriate, on a technical basis in the promotion of activities of existing out-of-court bodies and in the establishment of new bodies; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) andma vajaduse korral liikmesriikidele tehnilist abi olemasolevate kohtuv&auml;liste organite tegevuse edendamiseks ja uute organite loomiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) take action to facilitate the networking of the national central points to form a Community-wide extra-judicial network designed to facilitate the out-of-court settlement of transborder disputes; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) v&otilde;tma meetmeid, et h&otilde;lbustada riiklike kontaktpunktide v&otilde;rgustiku loomist, moodustamaks kogu &uuml;hendust h&otilde;lmavat kohtuv&auml;list v&otilde;rku, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on h&otilde;lbustada riikidevaheliste vaidluste kohtuv&auml;list lahendamist; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) support the above network, in accordance with Decision No 283/1999/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 25 January 1999 establishing a general framework for Community activities in favour of consumers(2), and within the limits of the financial framework determined therein; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) toetama eespool nimetatud v&otilde;rku koosk&otilde;las Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu 25. jaanuari 1999. aasta otsusega 283/1999/E&Uuml; (millega luuakse tarbijaid puudutava &uuml;henduse tegevuse &uuml;ldine raamistik) (2) ja selles m&auml;&auml;ratletud finantsraamistiku piires; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) support on a techncial basis the setting up and coordination of national central points, in particular by means of technical devices for on-line communication and translation facilities; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) toetama tehniliselt riiklike kontaktpunktide loomist ja nende t&ouml;&ouml; koordineerimist, eelk&otilde;ige sidussuhtluse ja t&otilde;lkimisseadmete jaoks vajalike tehniliste vahendite abil; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) develop in close cooperation with Member States common criteria for the assessment of out-of-court bodies falling outside the scope of Recommendation 98/257/EC; these criteria should ensure, inter alia, the quality, fairness and effectiveness of such bodies; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) arendama tihedas koost&ouml;&ouml;s liikmesriikidega v&auml;lja &uuml;hised kriteeriumid soovituse 98/257/E&Uuml; reguleerimisalasse mittekuuluvate kohtuv&auml;liste organite hindamiseks; need kriteeriumid peaksid muu hulgas tagama selliste organite taseme, &otilde;igluse ja t&otilde;hususe; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) consider also encouraging out-of-court bodies and central points to develop, as far as possible, practical arrangements in favour of the consumer, inter alia, where appropirate, the use of - especially where a contract has been concluded at a distance - a written or on-line procedure, in particular in transfrontier dispute settlement, so as to avoid the need for the consumer to travel. </inglise>
<eesti> 6) kaaluma ka kohtuv&auml;liste organite ja kontaktpunktide julgustamist, et arendada v&otilde;imalikult suures ulatuses v&auml;lja tarbijale kasulik praktiline kord, millele v&otilde;ib vajaduse korral muu hulgas lisada, eriti kui tegemist on kauglepinguga, kirjaliku v&otilde;i sidusmenetluse ja seda eelk&otilde;ige piiri&uuml;lese vaidluste lahendamise korral, et tarbijal ei oleks vaja reisida; </eesti>
<inglise> 12. </inglise>
<eesti> 12. </eesti>
<inglise> INVITES Member States to keep the Commission regularly informed of the development of national bodies and central points; INVITES the Commission to report regularly to the Council on the development of an EEJ-Net and other more specialised networks established for similar purposes. </inglise>
